author: Harshith Traders
text:
Just a prototype.... Not feasible.

India cannot afford such expensive infra.. the cost is too much and moreover there are high chances that the pores or holes will block soon due to algae formation. Over the period of time after sun and water exposure...the life of pipe and plastic connection will torn out. 
So ...just a gimmick.. but not a feasible and durable option to farmers.

reply.author: Usman Khan
reply.text: Agree , very bad design , some pvc are hardy they may last decades or can b covered with soil but the soft rubber is fragile it will not survive more then 2 year , i think its good for small scale and one advantage is that it will save some water , but i feel its waste of money if u see durability and covering whole area with piping , i think still better would b installing long range sprinklers at corners, it will cover large area from ends without spending on piping and it will b forever . drip system is best in vegetables that dont need spraying , i think govts should subsidize these things so it saves water , hence more farmers can use that water and produce more , in subcont we dont think water as commodity thats the problem , or if u add up all the saving , its still feasible these systems .
